}}</ref> Genotype Z emerged in 2002 through [[reassortment]] from earlier highly pathogenic genotypes of H5N1<ref name=KSLi/> that first infected birds in [[China]] in 1996, and first infected humans in [[Hong Kong]] in 1997.<ref name=Kou/><ref name=WHOinfluenza/><ref name=WHOtimeline>

